    <note>Shao(2) Bowen [20864] When Zhang(2) Dun [333] became chief minister in Shaosheng period, he tried to bring Bowen into his administration since he had once studied with Bowen's father, Yong [3718]. Bowen declined the offer 100 times. When Zhao(1) Huizong [9008] was enthroned, there was an eclipse of the sun and Bowen responded to the edict requesting criticism (literally words 'yan') by recommending that the institutions of the founders be restored and that the new emperor discriminate between junzi and xiaoren in his employment of advisors. CBD, 2, 1330-31.</note>
